what is DynamoDB?
## **Amazon DynamoDB (Interview-Ready Explanation)**
Amazon Web Services DynamoDB is a fully managed NoSQL database service provided by AWS.

It is designed for high performance, scalability, and low-latency applications.
DynamoDB stores data in key-value and document format instead of traditional tables with complex joins.
AWS automatically handles scaling, backups, and maintenance.
It is commonly used in real-time applications, gaming, IoT, and shopping carts.
It can handle millions of requests per second without server management.

**Example:**
In an e-commerce application, DynamoDB can store user shopping cart data so that users can quickly add or remove products in real time.
